# Find & install skills

When user wants installable agent skills (not just repo rules):

## When to use

- "Find a skill for …", "is there a skill …", "how do I do X" where X is common packaged workflow
- Wants to extend agent with domain packs (design, deploy, review, etc.)

## CLI

`npx skills` — package manager for open skills ecosystem.

- `npx skills find [query]` — search
- `npx skills add <package>` — install
- `npx skills check` / `npx skills update` — maintenance
- Browse: https://skills.sh/

## Flow

1. Domain + task from user message
2. Check leaderboard https://skills.sh/ for popular match
3. Run `npx skills find <keywords>` if needed
4. Before recommend: prefer **1k+ installs**, reputable org (`vercel-labs`, `anthropics`, `microsoft`), sane GitHub stars
5. Reply with: name, what it does, install command, link

Install example: `npx skills add <owner/repo@skill> -g -y` (global; user confirms).

## Empty results

Say none found; offer help without skill; `npx skills init my-skill` if they repeat the workflow.
